{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52fb878f-b5d2-45a1-875a-6ccc6f8801ee","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's general guidance:\n\n**Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` using `dotnet test`:**\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n1. **Enable the new platform** — add this to each test `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\n2. **TRX reports** — the `--logger trx` argument still works; publish them with:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n   ```\n\n3. **Code coverage** — `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` still works. Publish with:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n\n4. **Drop `VSTest@3`** entirely — it's not needed with `dotnet test` driving the new test platform.\n\nThe rest of your pipeline (build, publish artifacts, etc.) stays the same.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"453f903a-059d-4ff7-adab-f78d62d4e3df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no repository content here. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":435,"requestId":"7C22:9A1BB:2702FCC:2B0D044:69F93EF5"},"id":"2867cc1d-03b0-43b1-9aa4-409d31da0ae1","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:10.101Z","parentId":"27cb6eea-71ac-4091-b9f3-c1977ac675f1"}
